FireRedTTS-2 — Japanese dialogue fork
=====================================

This repository is a fork of FireRedTTS-2 by FireRedTeam
(https://github.com/FireRedTeam/FireRedTTS2), distributed under the
Apache License 2.0. See the LICENSE file for the full license text.

Modifications in this fork (abePclWaseda / kobas-lab, 2026):

- fireredtts2/fireredtts2.py
    Added an `output_stereo` option to `FireRedTTS2.generate_dialogue`.
    When True, it returns turn-separated stereo [2, T] (S1/S3 -> left,
    S2/S4 -> right) instead of the default mono [1, T]. The per-turn audio
    is identical to the mono path; only the final channel assembly differs.
    The default (False) preserves the original upstream behavior.

- dialogue_tools/  (new directory)
    Easy-inference and post-processing tools built on the public API only
    (no changes to the core model are required to use them):
      synthesize.py         stereo/mono dialogue synthesis + per-turn timing
                            manifest + per-turn audio segments
      postprocess.py        overlap engineering / backchannel insertion,
                            applied by re-timing the manifest (no re-generation)
      synth_backchannel.py  synthesize backchannels (aizuchi) in a speaker's
                            voice, for insertion on the listener's channel

Japanese-finetuned weights are published separately on Hugging Face:
    kobas-lab/fireredtts2-zoom1-dialogue-ja
(assembled on top of the base FireRedTeam/FireRedTTS2 checkpoints).

Model weights are NOT included in this repository.
